definition.value: A tripeptide composed of L-glutamic acid, L-arginine, and glycine joined in sequence by peptide linkages.
A cineole in which the 1,8-cineole skeleton is substituted at C-2 with a hydroxy group oriented exo (S configuration).
An alpha-amino acid that consists of 2-amino-3-oxo-4-hydroxybutanoic acid in which the hydrogen of the hydroxy function is substituted by a phospho group.
